RURAL COASTAL LIVING
Nestled on the edge of a little country town and set on 1,124m2 approx (over quarter acre) block zoned 'Commercial'. This fantastic home is only 12 km from San Remo fishing village and bridge. The home is only 3 years old and is well designed with 9 ft ceilings.
Spacious living zones and is light and bright throughout.
Comprising 3 bedrooms, master with large ensuite and walk in robe. Centrally located hostess kitchen complete with beautiful stone bench tops and adjoining butlers pantry.
An open plan dining area and separate family living area completes this ideal package. Extra features include :
2nd bathroom, split system, wood fire and ceiling fans throughout.
PLUS
- 2 X 23,500 litre water tanks, servicing the house and garden (no town water).
- Insulated floors, roof and walls.
- 26 panel solar, equivalent to 7 kilowatts power.
- Permanent gutter guard.
- Porch - full length of home on one side.
- Newly installed Visage roll down, spring loaded blinds.
- Variety of fruit trees.
- Garden Shed.
- 4 car garage - roller door.
- 4 x carport, covered in 3 sides, bay opening doors.

Description:
Affordable Coastal Lifestyle
BUILDING BLOCKS FROM 700sqm to over 1000sqm.
Living by the water isn’t just for the rich and famous.
Why not join the growing number of savvy baby boomers who are discovering the charms of Bass Coast’s best kept secret – Corinella.
This quaint, scenic coastal village offers residents an all year round relaxed, holiday feel.
It’s ideal for boating, fishing and hiking enthusiasts, or those desiring a quiet, layback coastal lifestyle. These beautiful blocks have water views, are neighboured by quality new homes and there is no time restrictions on building, so you can secure land today and build in a few years.
Located just a few minutes off the Bass Coast highway, you’re only about a 20 minute drive from Philip Island, 25 minutes to Cranbourne or approx. 90 minutes to Melbourne CBD. Whatever your reason for a sea change, be quick to snap up a block today before these land prices go soaring.
Blocks ranging from $160,000 to $300,000

Description:
UNDER OFFER
This modest 2 bedroom home comprises built-in robes, bathroom, kitchen, wood-heater, some furniture and 17 usable acres of beautiful French Island land. Other features include a Lister 5kva power generator, shedding, excellent cattle-yards, two dams a big paddock and creek access for a small boat.
French Island is approximately two thirds national park and is unincorporated, therefore is not governed by a local council, so no council rates apply. Being off the grid, means there are no power companies to deal with and no water rates to pay. About an hour from Melbourne, but like stepping back in time, we are a small community of around 100 residents, accessable by passenger ferry from Stony Point, or vehicle barge from Corinella.
Please contact Phil on 5980 1234 to discuss this unique opportunity.

Description:
ALL THE WHISTLES & BELLS!
$549,000 Negotiable
Tucked away in a beautiful private setting abutting the National Park, sits this 60 ACRES with well-equipped, proud home, ready for your French Island lifestyle. Comprising 3 spacious bedrooms, including master with walk-in robe and ensuite, this lovely country home also has a lounge, dining room, family room, chefs kitchen and large entertaining deck, all overlooking the water and spectacular sunsets.
This established property also has all the mod cons one would expect in the city, but set high on Mount Wellington. Features include reverse cycle split system air-conditioning, gas cooking, dishwasher, a huge dam, 4 bay garage, multiple workshops, 75,000 litres of water storage, 11kva Lister generator, 2kw solar panels and a fire system.
Other items for consideration, include a large caravan, tractor, boat, vehicles and even a tip-truck!
French Island is a unique environment, less than 80km from Melbourne, but with no council to enforce council-rates. We are a population of approximately 100 residents and over 1000 koalas! The air is fresh and the birdlife spectacular. Please contact Phil for further details, or to arrange a private inspection. Ph: 0438 497 715

Description:
Perfect Investment
This family sized home, is a new listing on the market and comprises of 3 spacious sized bedrooms. The master has a walk in robe and full ensuite. There are two generous sized living areas, with a functional kitchen and walk in pantry, glass top electric cooking, breakfast bar and vinyl floored meals area. The home is heated by a wood heater and reverse cycle split system. There is a linen closet and a walk in storage closet.
The property is one of the bigger residential sized blocks and offers a two car under roof carport, connected driveway and parking, in front of the two car garage and workshop area, plus a large lawn backyard and under roof entertainment area leading outside from the kitchen meals area with sliding door access.
The perfect property for both the owner occupier that wants a bigger block or for an investment property as the property is currently tenanted.

Description:
Rosebery Cottage
Looking behind the picket fence and cottage gardens you will fall in love with the oozing warmth and character of yesteryear complimenting this beautifully renovated home on a 623m2 block all ready for you to move straight in. Home boasts a cosy living with soaring vaulted (coach) ceilings and Baltic pine features plus gas log fire for those cold winters' nights plus a split system for Summer. The kitchen was recently renovated and has an abundance of cupboards plus you have 4 bedrooms with main renovated bathroom serving also as an ensuite to master bedroom. Outside you have wide driveway with carport and second toilet ideal for entertaining. Ideal location and close to everything this property is sure to impress and won't last long

Description:
ENTRY LEVEL OPPORTUNITY! BE QUICK
Let your creative juices flow at 'Koala Station', a character filled, quaint and quirky weatherboard cottage comprising polished floorboards, cathedral ceilings, wood heater, gas cook top and oven, one large master bedroom and a two bedroom train carriage positioned off the platform-styled rear deck
Also includes a large colorbond shed, 2 large rainwater tanks, a kids tree-house, some maze-like tracks through the bush-garden and the restored train carriage. An added bonus is plenty of fire-wood already cut with lots more wood on the property and some vehicles for use on the property.
Ideal as an artists hideaway and/or as a base from which to travel.
French Island is approximately two thirds national park and is unincorporated, therefore is not governed by a local council, so no council rates apply. Being off the grid, means there are no power companies to deal with and no water rates to pay. About an hour from Melbourne, but like stepping back in time, we are a small community of around 100 residents, accessible by passenger ferry from Stony Point, or vehicle barge from Corinella.
Please contact Phil on 5980 1234 to discuss this unique opportunity.

Description:
UNDER OFFER
FOR SALE BY SET DATE 3rd July 2016 if not sold prior. Wow, this is one of the neatest and best presented quality homes you will see and only a few minutes walk to the town center and primary school. Perfect for a large family, day care or dual occupation with two zones of living. Set on a whopping 1085m2 (over 1/4 acre) block, this stunning home is approximately 28 squares of living with a 6 square entertainment area, five good sized bedrooms with a good size master bedroom with a full ensuite, walk in robe and ceiling fan, all other bedrooms have built in robes and ceiling fans. You will find the step down front formal lounge has a real open fire place and brick feature wall and steps up to the formal dining area, flowing through to the spacious kitchen with new cabinets and appliances including a 900ml stainless steel oven and range hood, dishwasher, wide breakfast bar and garden window views of the very attractive alfresco area. The meals area is spacious and leads through to the generous size rumpus room with wood fire heating and natural gas ducted heating.
The alfresco area (approx. 6sqs) is a beautiful outside living area which has been paved and is perfect for private entertaining. The double garage under roofline has roller door access from the alfresco area. The large block has plenty of space with a bungalow/workshop and is still large enough for children to play, space for veggie garden and outdoor activities. Agent available 7 days a week

Description:
OLDY BUT A GOODY!!!
Full of old time charm, this property is the ideal home or getaway.
Featuring 3 bedrooms, a spacious timber kitchen with meals area and polished timber floors, a good sized lounge room with ceiling fans, split system and wood heater, a modern family bathroom and external laundry.
An undercover verandah at the rear of the house is ideal for entertaining and the established garden houses a double shed with power and lights. To the side of the house is a single carport with roller door.
Situated in a quiet location next to the park and close to the beach, this property is within 5 mins of local services, shops, cafes and wineries.
